 **Never** ignore an escalation or force the same model to retry without changes. If the implementer said it's stuck, something needs to change.

+## Review Loop Limits
+
+- **Max iterations:** 10 for any review loop (spec compliance or code quality). After 10 iterations with unresolved critical or important issues, escalate to the user.
+- **Minor issues don't block:** Note them in the task completion report but proceed to the next task. Do not loop on minor-only feedback.
+- **Same-issue cap:** If the same issue appears in 3 consecutive review cycles, escalate — the implementer and reviewer disagree on how to fix it.
+
+## Prose Cleanup Pass
+
+Every task ends with a prose cleanup pass. This is not optional. Run after code-quality review reaches zero critical and zero important findings, before marking the task complete:
+
+1. Strip every comment that restates what the code does (`// Initialize the logger`, `// Return the result`).
+2. Strip AI-obvious phrases — apply `humanizer` patterns. No "ensures proper...", "leverages...", "facilitates...", "serves as...", no significance inflation, no rule-of-three padding.
+3. Rewrite remaining comments, docstrings, and error messages so they sound like a person wrote them. Direct and specific. No filler.
+4. Keep only comments that explain *why* code does something a non-obvious way — a hidden constraint, an invariant, a workaround.
+
+The implementer subagent runs this pass itself before reporting the task complete. The controller does not advance to the next task until the pass is reported as done.
+
+## Pre-Merge User Review
+
+After the final code reviewer approves and before invoking `finishing-a-development-branch`, give the user a ready-to-run diff command so they can review all changes from their own terminal:
+
+```
+To review the full diff before we proceed:
+
+  git diff main...<worktree-branch>
+```
+
+Replace `<worktree-branch>` with the actual branch name. Three-dot (`main...<branch>`) shows only the changes introduced on the branch, even if main has advanced. Use branch-based diff, not path-based (`git -C <worktree-path> diff`).
+
+Wait for the user to confirm before continuing to the finishing skill. If the user requests changes, address them and re-present the diff command.
+
+## Polish Dispatch (End-of-Plan)
+
+After the final code reviewer approves and the user confirms the diff, dispatch the `post-implementation-polish` skill against the full implementation before invoking `finishing-a-development-branch`. The plan header's `**Polish:**` line names the rules the polish subagent loads. See the `executing-plans` skill's `## Polish Phase` for iteration limits.
+
